review_blob: A very dark and smoky porter. Poured in to a Libbey Porter/Stout glass. Looks beautiful with a thick off-white head. Carbonation is just right in my opinion. Flavor got more complex as the beer warmed up. Would definitely repeat.

Poured in to a snifter. Dark almost black color with about 1 1/2 finger head. Chocolate aroma with some Coffee as well. Carbonated just right with chocolate coffee and dark fruit flavors. Great Russian Imperial Stout.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Was a lot more pleasant than expected. Was kind of reluctant to buy because I am not a licorice fan but this one is well balanced. This just became one of my top stouts!
Excellent one from cigar city...smooth taste and well balanced. One of the top ambers!
From bottle to tulip. Beautiful looking reddish gold brown color. Aroma was spicy with hops. I am saying it is a good beer but not my style. I prefer IPAs and belgiums over an american ale.
Drank from bottle. Just a well balanced beer. Some of Belgiums finest work. Smooth & easy to drink.
My first Heavy Seas beer. Quit delightful flavor very robust, crisp, suggests citrus. Definitely buying this one again.
Had a nice citrus aroma pretty lively palate but did not enjoy the taste too much for this IPA. I do not think I will purchase this one again though.
Well balanced IPA Dogfish Head knows what they are doing. Crisp hoppy bold flavor not a strong alcohol taste. One of my favorites!
Chocolate, coffee, nuts aroma medium bitter and pretty creamy. I enjoyed this one and cant wait to try other Cigar City selections.
beer_name: Cigar City Jos Mart American Porter

review_blob: Meant to buy the  The Alchemist / Ninkasi / Stone More Brown than Black IPA but bought this one instead but was not disappointed at all. Nice pumpkin spiced beer.
beer_name: Bruery / Elysian / Stone La Citrueille Cleste de Citracado

review_blob: One of my first Belgian beers. Doughy earthy aroma. Golden Hazy appearance. Taste had a subtle bitterness but wonderful overall. On my top 10!

beer_name: Terrapin Wake-n-Bake Coffee Oatmeal Imperial Stout

review_blob: Drank from bottle. Aroma was pleasant, slightly heavy bitterness but tasted great. Over was satisfied with this one!
Drank out of the bottle. Spicy, caramel aromas. Well balanced taste with little aftertaste. Overall an awesome beer.
Delightful, will continue to buy this one.  Floral, bread, earthy aroma. Medium sweetness light bitterness. Lively carbonation overall pleasant. Victory wins again!
